  "prompt": "Has Voyager-1 confirmed that there are no Planet X and Nemesis star?",
  "response": "Voyager 1, the spacecraft launched by NASA in 1977, has not specifically confirmed the absence of a Planet X or Nemesis star. Its mission was primarily to explore the outer planets of our solar system, and after completing its primary mission, it has been journeying into interstellar space, sending back data about the heliosphere and the interstellar medium. \n\nThe existence of Planet X (a hypothetical additional planet in our solar system) or the Nemesis star (a hypothetical companion star to the Sun) has not been confirmed or denied by Voyager 1 because its instruments and trajectory are not explicitly designed for detecting such objects. \n\nThe search for these hypothetical bodies is typically conducted using different methods, such as astronomical surveys with ground-based or space telescopes. While Voyager 1 contributes valuable data about the outer reaches of our solar system and beyond, the question of Planet X and Nemesis remains primarily in the realm of telescope-based observations and theoretical astrophysics.",
